@CustomerOrder_HostAddress = http://localhost:5044
@AuthService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5170

### ========================================
### AUTHENTICATION
### ========================================
### IMPORTANT: Run this first to get JWT token, then copy the token below
### Or manually set @token variable with your JWT token

### 0. Login to get JWT Token
# @name login
POST {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### After running the login request above, copy the token from response and paste it below
### Or if using VS Code REST Client, it will auto-capture from the response above
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..N0b_-C1_3EBLzUjCX3IuGZnUxBkC6xIRk6O-XPtOLh8


### ========================================
### CUSTOMER ENDPOINTS
### ========================================

### 1. Create Customer - John Doe
POST {{CustomerOrder_HostAddress}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "phoneNumber": "555-0100",
  "address": "123 Main St, New York, NY 10001"
}

### 2. Create Customer - Jane Smith
POST {{CustomerOrder_HostAddress}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "phoneNumber": "555-0101",
  "address": "456 Oak Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90001"
}

### 3. Create Customer - Bob Johnson
POST {{CustomerOrder_HostAddress}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json
